{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking dish, sharp knife, aluminium foil, oven","id":"r239602","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-c8XODCRXrcE\/XZVRMq0nfqI\/AAAAAAAAdLM\/njHp712Z0pYdKWENpggDFyJ_mPN1CTv_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hlzjkBc7-ce98OWZ.png","title":"Stuffed Courgettes - Zucchine farcite","publishedAt":"2018-05-28T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"4 courgettes, large"},{"content":"90 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"content":"60 g bread, torn in pieces"},{"content":"15 g fresh mint leaves"},{"content":"120 g red onions, quartered"},{"content":"30 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"12 green olives, pitted"},{"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"content":"2 medium eggs"},{"content":"80 g ricotta cheese"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"23.5 g","fat":"24 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13.5 g","calories":"1585 kJ \/ 380 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C and grease a large baking dish or tray."},{"content":"Slice courgettes in half lengthways. With a small sharp knife, make an incision 5 mm around the edge then diagonally score and scoop out the flesh and reserve. Place courgette shells in prepared baking dish."},{"content":"Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place bread and mint in mixing bowl then chop <b>Turbo\/2 sec\/2 times<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>4 sec\/speed 4.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add reserved courgette flesh, olives, salt and pepper, chop <b>1 sec\/speed 4<b> then cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed <b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool."},{"content":"Place eggs, 60 g reserved Parmesan and ricotta in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add 50 g reserved breadcrumbs and cooled courgette mixture then mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Stir with spatula then mix again <b>5 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Fill courgette shells with mixture."},{"content":"Combine remaining breadcrumbs with remaining grated Parmesan then sprinkle over filled courgettes. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes (200°C), removing foil 5 minutes before the end of cooking time."},{"content":"Remove from oven and leave to rest for a few minutes before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Courgettes, from the French word <i>courge<\/i>, meaning 'squash', are a summer squash that is harvested before it is fully grown. For this recipe, the insides have been hollowed out before being stuffed with familiar Italian ingredients: creamy ricotta, fresh mint and salty olives. Topped with breadcrumbs and baked in the oven, these stuffed courgettes are a deliciously light and flavoursome main.","To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan cheese for a vegetarian hard cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}